# Logger 26: High-Performance POTA Logging

> **The lightweight, high-performance logging terminal designed for the modern portable operator.**

Built to target the **UWP standards**, Logger 26 offers a "zero-bloat" experience for **POTA**, **SOTA**, or mobile **HF/VHF** operations.

---

###  Core Features

* **Rapid QSO Entry**
    Log callsigns, frequency, mode, RST, and power with minimal taps. Timestamps are fully automated so you can stay focused on the pileup.
* **Smart Band & Mode Detection**
    Intelligently maps frequencies to bands to reduce manual entry errors and speed up your workflow.
* **CW Haptic Engine**
    A unique tactile feedback system. Confirm callsigns and status signals via **Morse code vibration**—perfect for bright sunlight where screens are hard to read.
* **Session History**
    View and verify your 5 most recent QSOs at a glance for quick on-the-fly corrections.
* **Windows 10 Live Tiles**
    Integration with the Metro UI allows you to view your latest contacts directly on your home screen.

---

### Why Logger 26 is Different

While other apps are filled with trackers and insecure storage, **Logger 26** is built from the ground up for the security-conscious operator:

* **Hardware-Backed Encryption**
    Your QRZ credentials aren't just saved; they are encrypted using **AES-GCM** within the Windows Password Vault.
* **Zero Telemetry**
    No ads, no analytics, and no third-party tracking. Your data stays strictly between you and QRZ.com.
* ** Native & Modern**
    Optimized for the **Windows 10 Mobile Metro UI**. It feels like a native part of your OS, not an afterthought.
* ** Privacy-First**
    Forced **HTTPS (TLS 1.3)** for all transmissions.

> [!TIP]
> **Only Modern Cloud Native Ham radio software currently available for Windows 10 Mobile.**

---

###  Distribution & Installation

Logger 26 removes the "digital friction" of logging, allowing you to focus on the radio, not the screen.

* **Format:** Distributed as a lightweight `.appxbundle` **universal* binary** for manual sideloading.
* **Compatibility:** Designed Mobile-first for ARM, with an experimental X86 compatibility layer.

